        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"626349\">Asei Inoue</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/regression.20of.20.60exact.3F.60/near/564037697\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>this suggestion is too much complicated...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Different versions recommend different fixes without clarifying why a particular one is the default. When you update, the old default might break, forcing you to find a new fix through a new \"exact?\". It's mostly based on experience—I don't have a specific example, as it's just something that happens occasionally.</p>",
